

Examples -
===========


- If we want to Get Selected Data from the Table we can do that as below
SELECT customer_id, customer_fname, customer_city, customer_state FROM customers;



- If we want to Check the Structure of the Table we can use the below Command
DESC customers;  OR DESCRIBE customers;



- if we want to check the tables like what kind of data we have so we can use below with Limit the Columns like 5,10, 15 20 depends upon you
SELECT * FROM customers LIMIT 5;


- if we want to Sort the Data on the Basis of Customer First-Name
SELECT * FROM customers ORDER BY customer_fname;  [This will Show Data in ASC Order]



- For Descending Order we can use below
SELECT * FROM customers ORDER BY customer_fname DESC; 



- The Below Command will delete the Table as well as the Entire Data
DROP TABLE customers; 



- If we want to Only Delete the Information Inside the table then we can use the below Command
DELETE TABLE employees;


